                            <comment id="384969" author="pjones" created="Wed, 6 Sep 2023 13:09:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Landed for 2.16&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="384891" author="gerrit" created="Wed, 6 Sep 2023 06:15:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&quot;Oleg Drokin &amp;lt;green@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&quot; merged in patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/52090/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/52090/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17052&quot; title=&quot;inux-prim.c:129:25: error: dereferencing pointer to incomplete type &#8216;struct xa_node&#8217;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-17052&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-17052&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; libcfs: fix build for old kernel&lt;br/&gt;
Project: fs/lustre-release&lt;br/&gt;
Branch: master&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: &lt;br/&gt;
Commit: 75dd69dd6ecac38267a8fbf475945b2a2f293ba9&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="383684" author="gerrit" created="Fri, 25 Aug 2023 03:42:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&quot;xinliang &amp;lt;xinliang.liu@linaro.org&amp;gt;&quot; uploaded a new patch: &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/52090&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/52090&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17052&quot; title=&quot;inux-prim.c:129:25: error: dereferencing pointer to incomplete type &#8216;struct xa_node&#8217;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-17052&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-17052&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; libcfs: fix build for old kernel&lt;br/&gt;
Project: fs/lustre-release&lt;br/&gt;
Branch: master&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: 1&lt;br/&gt;
Commit: faab3d6bd3d898b6e849705476318e82210a7c09&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="383683" author="xinliang" created="Fri, 25 Aug 2023 03:09:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This break build might affect old kernel from v4.17 to v4.19. Because v4.17 adds &amp;lt;linux/xarray.h&amp;gt; and make fs.h #include&#160; &amp;lt;linux/xarray.h&amp;gt;, v4.20 introduces full xarray support.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The cause is that fs.h(from kernel v4.17 commit b93b016313b3) is already included &amp;lt;linux/xarray.h&amp;gt;, so #include &amp;lt;libcfs/linux/xarray.h&amp;gt; which contains the definition of &apos;struct xa_node&apos;&#160; don&apos;t take effect.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
cat libcfs/libcfs/linux/linux-prim.c
...
#include &amp;lt;linux/fs.h&amp;gt;
...
#ifndef HAVE_XARRAY_SUPPORT
#include &amp;lt;libcfs/linux/xarray.h&amp;gt;
#endif &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
